\hypertarget{algorithm-4-random-forest-regressor-yield-prediction}{%
\subsubsection{3.3.4 Algorithm 4 --- Random Forest Regressor (Yield
Prediction)}\label{algorithm-4-random-forest-regressor-yield-prediction}}

\hypertarget{regression-vs.-classification}{%
\paragraph{\texorpdfstring{\textbf{Regression vs.
Classification}}{Regression vs. Classification}}\label{regression-vs.-classification}}

\begin{quote}
While crop recommendation uses Random Forest for \textbf{classification}
(predicting a discrete crop name), yield prediction uses it for
\textbf{regression} (predicting a continuous numerical value ---
production in Quintals).

For regression, each tree outputs a numeric value, and the final
prediction is the \textbf{mean} across all trees:

ŷ = (1/B) * Σ(t=1 to B) ŷ\_t(x)

Where ŷ\_t(x) is the prediction of the t-th tree for input x.
\end{quote}

\hypertarget{one-hot-encoding}{%
\paragraph{\texorpdfstring{\textbf{One-Hot
Encoding}}{One-Hot Encoding}}\label{one-hot-encoding}}

\begin{quote}
Categorical columns (State\_Name, District\_Name, Season, Crop) are
converted using \textbf{OneHotEncoder}. Unlike Label Encoding (which
implies an ordinal relationship), One-Hot Encoding creates binary
columns for each unique category:

Season: {[}"Kharif", "Rabi", "Whole Year"{]}

→ {[}1, 0, 0{]} for Kharif

→ {[}0, 1, 0{]} for Rabi

→ {[}0, 0, 1{]} for Whole Year

This prevents the model from incorrectly interpreting "Rabi
\textgreater{} Kharif" due to label ordering.
\end{quote}

\hypertarget{regression-evaluation-metrics}{%
\paragraph{\texorpdfstring{ \textbf{Regression Evaluation
Metrics}}{ Regression Evaluation Metrics}}\label{regression-evaluation-metrics}}

\begin{longtable}[]{@{}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\columnwidth - 4\tabcolsep) * \real{0.3333}}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\columnwidth - 4\tabcolsep) * \real{0.3333}}
  >{\raggedright\arraybackslash}p{(\columnwidth - 4\tabcolsep) * \real{0.3333}}@{}}
\toprule()
\begin{minipage}[b]{\linewidth}\raggedright
\textbf{Metric}
\end{minipage} & \begin{minipage}[b]{\linewidth}\raggedright
\textbf{Formula}
\end{minipage} & \begin{minipage}[b]{\linewidth}\raggedright
\textbf{Meaning}
\end{minipage} \\
\midrule()
\endhead
R² Score & 1 - (SS\_res / SS\_tot) & Proportion of variance explained by
the model \\
MAE & `(1/n) * Σ & y\_i - ŷ\_i \\
RMSE & \(\sqrt{}\lbrack(1/n)\ *\ \Sigma\ (y\_ i\  - \ ŷ\_ i)²\rbrack\) &
Square root of mean squared error \\
MAPE & `(1/n) * Σ & (y\_i - ŷ\_i)/y\_i \\
\bottomrule()
\end{longtable}

