\hypertarget{implementation}{%
\subsection{3.5 Implementation}\label{implementation}}

\begin{quote}
The implementation of AGROPORTAL is divided into three distinct user
modules to cater to different user groups, ensuring a centralized yet
secure environment for all agricultural transactions.
\end{quote}

\hypertarget{farmer-module}{%
\subsubsection{3.5.1 Farmer Module}\label{farmer-module}}

\begin{quote}
The Farmer Module is the primary functional component, providing a
dashboard for all decision-support tools. Upon secure login ---
facilitated by two-factor authentication via email OTP --- farmers can
access:
\end{quote}

\begin{itemize}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  \textbf{AI Intelligence Hub:} A unified tab-based interface providing:
  \end{quote}
\end{itemize}

\begin{itemize}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  Crop Recommendation (NPK + climate → crop suggestion)
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  Fertilizer Advisory (soil conditions + crop type → fertilizer)
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  Regional Crop Prediction (state/district/season → best crops)
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  Yield Estimator (geography + crop + area → production in Quintals)
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  Rainfall Tool (region + month → historical average mm)
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  AI Chatbot (free-form queries addressed by Groq LLM)
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  Weather Dashboard (live 5-day forecast via OpenWeatherMap)
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  Agricultural News (real-time feed via NewsAPI)
  \end{quote}
\end{itemize}

\begin{itemize}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  \textbf{Product Management:} Farmers can add, edit, and remove their
  crop stock with pricing, available quantity, and product images.
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  \textbf{Orders Dashboard:} Farmers can view all incoming orders from
  customers and manage fulfillment status.
  \end{quote}
\end{itemize}

\hypertarget{customer-module}{%
\subsubsection{3.5.2 Customer Module}\label{customer-module}}

\begin{quote}
This module provides a marketplace for individual buyers or wholesalers.
Customers can browse available crops, check real-time stock levels, view
farmer details, and proceed to purchase directly. The module
incorporates:
\end{quote}

\begin{itemize}
\item
  A searchable and filterable product catalog
\item
  A shopping cart with persistent state
\item
  Checkout flow with order confirmation
\item
  Invoice generation for every successful transaction
\item
  Order history dashboard
\end{itemize}

\hypertarget{admin-module}{%
\subsubsection{3.5.3 Admin Module}\label{admin-module}}

\begin{quote}
The Administrative Module provides global oversight. The admin can:
\end{quote}

\begin{itemize}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  View and manage all registered farmers and customers
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  Monitor platform-wide crop availability and stock levels
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  Respond to user queries submitted through the "Contact Us" portal
  \end{quote}
\item
  \begin{quote}
  View system analytics --- total users, total orders, revenue trends
  \end{quote}
\end{itemize}

