\hypertarget{result}{%
\subsection{4.2 Result}\label{result}}

\begin{quote}
The system demonstrated high proficiency in delivering accurate
recommendations. The integration of various machine learning models
allowed the system to adapt to diverse data patterns. The Decision Tree
Classifier achieved the highest accuracy (88.5\%) in identifying
suitable crops based on regional data, while the Random Forest Regressor
demonstrated strong regression performance for yield prediction.
\end{quote}

\hypertarget{feature-importance-analysis}{%
\subsubsection{4.2.1 Feature Importance
Analysis}\label{feature-importance-analysis}}

\begin{quote}
Analyzing the features that most impact predictions:
\end{quote}

\textbf{For Crop Recommendation Interface (Random Forest Classifier):}

Analyzing the features that most impact crop recommendation predictions:

\begin{itemize}
\item
  Rainfall (mm) --- highest influence on crop suitability
\item
  Soil pH --- major factor affecting nutrient absorption and soil
  fertility
\item
  Nitrogen (N) content --- important for plant growth and leaf
  development
\item
  Temperature (°C) --- affects crop adaptability and growth cycle
\item
  Potassium (K) and Phosphorus (P) --- moderate influence on soil
  productivity
\item
  Humidity (\%) --- contextual impact depending on environmental
  conditions
\end{itemize}

\textbf{For Fertilizer Recommendation Interface (Decision Tree
Classifier):}

Analyzing the features that most impact fertilizer recommendation
predictions:

\begin{itemize}
\item
  Nitrogen (N), Phosphorus (P), and Potassium (K) levels --- strongest
  influence on fertilizer selection
\item
  Soil Moisture --- important for determining nutrient absorption
  capability
\item
  Soil Type --- affects fertilizer compatibility and soil retention
  capacity
\item
  Crop Type --- different crops require different nutrient compositions
\item
  Temperature (°C) --- influences fertilizer effectiveness and soil
  activity
\item
  Humidity (\%) --- contributes to environmental suitability for
  fertilizer usage
\end{itemize}

\textbf{For Regional Crop Prediction Interface (Decision Tree
Classifier):}

Analyzing the features that most impact regional crop prediction:

\begin{itemize}
\item
  Nitrogen (N), Phosphorus (P), and Potassium (K) levels --- strongest
  influence on fertilizer selection
\item
  Soil Moisture --- important for determining nutrient absorption
  capability
\item
  Soil Type --- affects fertilizer compatibility and soil retention
  capacity
\item
  Crop Type --- different crops require different nutrient compositions
\item
  Temperature (°C) --- influences fertilizer effectiveness and soil
  activity
\item
  Humidity (\%) --- contributes to environmental suitability for
  fertilizer usage
\end{itemize}

\textbf{For Yield Prediction Module Interface (Random Forest
Regressor):}

Analyzing the features that most impact regional crop prediction:

\begin{itemize}
\item
  Nitrogen (N), Phosphorus (P), and Potassium (K) levels --- strongest
  influence on fertilizer selection
\item
  Soil Moisture --- important for determining nutrient absorption
  capability
\item
  Soil Type --- affects fertilizer compatibility and soil retention
  capacity
\item
  Crop Type --- different crops require different nutrient compositions
\item
  Temperature (°C) --- influences fertilizer effectiveness and soil
  activity
\item
  Humidity (\%) --- contributes to environmental suitability for
  fertilizer usage
\end{itemize}

\textbf{For Weather Forecast Module Interface (OpenWeatherMap API-Based
Analysis)):}

Analyzing the weather parameters that most impact agricultural planning:

\begin{itemize}
\item
  Temperature (Max/Min) --- strongly affects crop growth and irrigation
  requirements
\item
  Humidity (\%) --- influences plant health and disease occurrence
\item
  Weather Condition --- important for farming activities such as sowing
  and harvesting
\item
