The user provides essential agricultural parameters such as Nitrogen
(N), Phosphorus (P), Potassium (K), temperature, humidity, soil
moisture, soil type, and crop type through the interactive interface.
After processing the input values using a trained Decision Tree--based
machine learning model, the system predicts and displays the recommended
fertilizer, such as DAP in this example. This module helps farmers apply
fertilizers more accurately, reducing excessive chemical usage and
improving soil fertility management. The user-friendly interface ensures
that farmers can easily obtain intelligent fertilizer recommendations
for better crop productivity and sustainable farming practices.
